source_segment: First, reset the authorization on your #PRS_ORG#

source_segment: Make sure the date and time settings on your #PRS_ORG# eReader are correct.

source_segment: Open #PRS_ORG# on your computer.

source_segment: Use #PRS_ORG# to delete the eBook that's causing issues from your #PRS_ORG# and your computer (make sure to choose the Remove from Library option).

source_segment: Click on your #PRS_ORG# under the "Devices" menu on the left.

source_segment: Click device options gear icon next to "Devices," then select Erase Device Authorization.
pe_segment: Cliquez sur l'icône d'engrenage des paramètres du périphérique à côté de « Périphériques », puis sélectionnez Effacer l'autorisation de périphérique.

source_segment: Click Erase Authorization, then OK to confirm.

source_segment: Try to reset the authorization in #PRS_ORG#

source_segment: In #PRS_ORG#, press Ctrl + Shift + D (Command + Shift + D on a Mac) on your keyboard.

source_segment: In the pop-up window that opens, enter the password for your #PRS_ORG# ID or #PRS_ORG# account (and make sure the correct #PRS_ORG# ID is listed in the drop-down menu).

source_segment: Authorize your computer again by going to Help > Authorize Computer.
